{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7c1a33ea-3ebd-4fcc-a3bd-9d58546a94e7","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n---\n\n**1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps**\n\nMSTest v4 changed the default **test-ID generation strategy** from `DisplayName` to `FullyQualifiedName`. Azure DevOps matches tests by ID, so every test looks new. To restore history, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n```\n\n**2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`**\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level** context — no test is running yet, so `TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException`. In v3 it silently returned a value, but that was conceptually wrong (class init runs once *before* any test). Fix your code by removing that access:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QM6e48TK8wzdAJu4n2fCnc","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dc676019f4ec499ca5396ec7307f130b/SetupTests.cs","old_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        var testName = context.TestName;\n        // Log setup for specific test\n    }","new_str":"    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n    {\n        // In MSTest v4 the ClassInitialize context is class-scoped;\n        // TestName is only available on the per-test context (e.g. in [TestInitialize]).\n    }"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-dc676019f4ec499ca5396ec7307f130b/SetupTests.cs."}],"interactionId":"75851c2e-4c3f-4f2c-8fc4-ca133c4af7a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I can see the user's code. Let me address their questions based on my knowledge of MSTest v4 breaking changes.\n\nKey MSTest v4 breaking changes:\n\n1. **Fully qualified test IDs** — MSTest v4 changed the default test ID format to use fully qualified names (namespace + class + method). This means Azure DevOps sees them as completely new tests, losing history. The workaround is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>` property.\n\n2. **TestContext in ClassInitialize** — In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a class-level context, not tied to any specific test. Accessing `TestContext.TestName` throws an `InvalidOperationException` because there's no test running yet at class-initialization time. \n\nThis was always conceptually wrong since class initialization runs once before all tests, but v3 silently returned a value anyway. Now v4 correctly throws an exception instead.\n\nBeyond these two issues, there are several other v4 changes worth keeping an eye on: `DeploymentItem` behavior has shifted, parallel execution defaults may differ, `TestContext.Properties` could work differently, Assert methods might enforce stricter validation, and the `DataRow` attribute has some changes. Let me walk through how to fix the specific code issues.","outputTokens":752,"requestId":"7C19:97105:176C9DB:1ACFD3D:69F95F59"},"id":"89a13670-5006-4c21-99f2-af346d7b2e3d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:09:27.967Z","parentId":"c7d8772f-4cbf-4729-9f75-c349f7651b76"}
