{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dde4196b-02d9-4e50-9791-6d1418597fec","content":"If you need per-test logging, move it to `[TestInitialize]` where `TestContext.TestName` is valid.\n\n---\n\n**Other v4 things to watch for:**\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **Assertions** | `Assert.ThrowsException` now requires an exact type match; subclass exceptions won't match. Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` or check with a catch. |\n| **`[DataRow]` type coercion** | Implicit type conversions (e.g., `int` → `long`) that v3 allowed may now fail. Match parameter types exactly. |\n| **Timeout behavior** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` co-operative cancellation by default rather than `Thread.Abort`. Long-running tests need to observe the token via `TestContext.CancellationTokenSource.Token`. |\n| **Parallel execution** | Class-level parallelism is now **on by default**. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]` or `DoNotParallelize` if tests have shared state. |\n| **`TestContext.Properties`** | The writable dictionary from v3 is now read-only in some scopes. |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75851c2e-4c3f-4f2c-8fc4-ca133c4af7a3","outputTokens":299,"requestId":"7C18:1E67:5D9988:6EBAC6:69F95F64"},"id":"2b609691-1abd-4097-b80b-e94e494796bf","timestamp":"2026-05-05T03:09:35.670Z","parentId":"dd8cc8af-6cba-493f-a568-af953c504923"}
